OL,3,CHow locker room chat became
OL,4,Ccontroversial for the US men's hockey
OL,5,Cteam
OL,7,FOn Tuesday night, the US president
OL,8,Fdelivered his annual State of the
OL,9,FUnion address at the Capitol in
OL,10,FWashington.
OL,12,FThe speech typically reports on the
OL,13,Fnation's budget, economy, news, and
OL,14,Fachievements, which this year included
OL,15,Fshoutouts for the Olympic teams.
OL,17,FThe president can invite guests of
OL,18,Fhonour to the address, and both the
OL,19,Fmen's and women's teams were invited,
OL,20,Fbut only the men attended.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1772041213
OL,3,CHow locker room chat became
OL,4,Ccontroversial for the US men's hockey
OL,5,Cteam
OL,7,FThe speech itself was the longest in
OL,8,Fhistory at around one hour and 48
OL,9,Fminutes, but Trump drew some of the
OL,10,Floudest applause when he invited the
OL,11,Fmen's hockey team into the House
OL,12,Fchamber.
OL,14,F"Our country is winning again. In
OL,15,Ffact, we're winning so much that we
OL,16,Freally don't know what to do about it.
OL,17,FPeople are asking me, 'Please, please,
OL,18,Fplease, Mr President, we're winning
OL,19,Ftoo much. We can't take it anymore,'"
OL,20,FTrump said before introducing the team.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31110
